   28        <h2><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/erinallard1/" target="_blank">Erin Allard, Instructor</a></h2>
   29:       <p class="justify">Erin Allard is Techtonica’s software engineering instructor and a Bay Area native who grew up in a working-class family. She earned her BA Economics from Mills College in Oakland, the oldest women’s college west of the Mississippi, and her MS International Real Estate from FIU in Miami. Feeling empowered to make a career switch, she graduated from Hackbright Academy’s software engineering fellowship and became an instructor for Girls Who Code. In addition to now teaching life-changing tech skills to Techtonica’s students, she and her wife co-host a podcast for women in tech called WITtalks.</p>
